                                                                    26 1451     
 Background                                                         26 1451     
 -------                                                            26 1451     
                                                                    26 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    26 1451     
 (LEIP) group at NC State University. The inelastic scattering      26 1451     
 thermal scattering law data for Be-metal were developed using      26 1451     
 established ab-initio lattice dynamics methods [1,2]. The LEAPR    26 1451     
 module from the NJOY code system was used to produce File 7 MT=2   26 1451     
 and 4 for Be-metal. Modifications to the LEAPR module were made    26 1451     
 to calculate the coherent elastic cross-section for Be-metal [3].  26 1451     
 Per convention, MAT=26 and ZA=126 are used for Be in Be-metal.     26 1451     
                                                                    26 1451     
 References                                                         26 1451     
 ----------                                                         26 1451     
                                                                    26 1451     
 1. A.I. Hawari, "Modern Techniques in Inelastic Thermal Neutron    26 1451     
    Scattering Analysis," Nuclear Data Sheets 118 (2014) 172.       26 1451     
 2. J.L. Wormald, A.I. Hawari "Thermal neutron scattering law       26 1451     
    calculations using ab initio molecular dynamics", EPJ Web of    26 1451     
    conferences 146, 13002 (2017)                                   26 1451     
 3. Y. Zhu, A.I. Hawari, "Implementation of a Generalized Coherent  26 1451     
    Elastic Scattering Formulation for Thermal Neutron Scattering   26 1451     
    Analysis," Proceedings of ICNC 2015: 35th International         26 1451     
    Conference on Nuclear Criticality Safety (2015).                26 1451     
